.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-UP" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.47" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-up \- Submit, watch, and stream logs in one command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose up [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Run the normal end\-to\-end workflow: optional preflight, image preparation, script rendering, sbatch submission or local launch, and immediate live watching with log streaming and exit\-code propagation.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--enroot\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the enroot executable. Default: enroot.
.TP
\fB--apptainer\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the apptainer executable. Default: apptainer.
.TP
\fB--singularity\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the singularity executable. Default: singularity.
.TP
\fB--keep\-failed\-prep\fR
Keep failed preparation state on disk for later inspection.
.TP
\fB--skip\-prepare\fR
Skip image import and prepare reuse checks.
.TP
\fB--force\-rebuild\fR
Refresh imported and prepared artifacts before running.
.TP
\fB--no\-preflight\fR
Skip the preflight phase before running.
.TP
\fB--script\-out\fR \fIOUTPUT\fR
Write the rendered launcher script to this path before submission or local launch.
.TP
\fB--sbatch\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sbatch executable. Default: sbatch.
.TP
\fB--srun\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the srun executable. Default: srun.
.TP
\fB--squeue\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the squeue executable. Default: squeue.
.TP
\fB--sacct\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sacct executable. Default: sacct.
.TP
\fB--local\fR
Launch the plan locally with Enroot instead of submitting it to Slurm.
.TP
\fB--allow\-resume\-changes\fR
Allow submission even when resume config drift is detected.
.TP
\fB--resume\-diff\-only\fR
Print the resume config diff and exit without preparing or submitting.
.TP
\fB--dry\-run\fR
Run preflight, prepare, and render without calling sbatch.
.TP
\fB--detach\fR
Submit or launch and return without watching logs.
.TP
\fB--watch\-queue\fR
After Slurm submission, poll queue state until the job reaches RUNNING before opening the watch view.
.TP
\fB--queue\-warn\-after\fR \fIDURATION\fR
Warn when \-\-watch\-queue stays PENDING longer than this duration; default is 10m, and 0 disables the warning.
.TP
\fB--watch\-mode\fR \fIMODE\fR
Watch output mode. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, tui, line.
.TP
\fB--hold\-on\-exit\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Keep the watch UI open after terminal states. Default: failure. Possible values: never, failure, always.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format for \-\-detach or \-\-dry\-run. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--print\-endpoints\fR
Include readiness\-derived service endpoints (host/port/url) and suggested next commands in the JSON output (with \-\-detach or \-\-dry\-run).
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose up \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose up \-\-detach \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose up \-\-detach \-\-format json \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose up \-\-detach \-\-format json \-\-print\-endpoints \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose up \-\-dry\-run \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose up \-\-watch\-mode line \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose up \-\-hold\-on\-exit always \-f compose.yaml
.fi
